# Walkthrough - Question Shuffling for Capitalization Game

I have implemented question shuffling for the Capitalization game to ensure that the order of questions is randomized each time a user starts the game.

## Changes Made

### Capitalization Game Logic
#### [capitalization.js](file:///d:/CHAD/GRAMMAR%20TREATS%20APRIL%209%20FINALE/Grammar%20Treatsv15.13/games/capitalization/capitalization.js)
- Added a `shuffleArray` function that implements the Fisher-Yates shuffle algorithm.
- Updated the `initGame` function to call `shuffleArray(questions)` before loading the first question.

```javascript
    function shuffleArray(array) {
        for (let i = array.length - 1; i > 0; i--) {
            const j = Math.floor(Math.random() * (i + 1));
            [array[i], array[j]] = [array[j], array[i]];
        }
    }

    // --- Start ---
    function initGame() {
        initAudio();
        shuffleArray(questions); // Randomizes the question order
        loadQuestion(0);
    }
```

## Verification Results

### Manual Verification
I verified the shuffling functionality by opening the game in a browser and refreshing the page multiple times. 

- **First Load:** The first question was "Mrs. Garcia, our English teacher...".
- **First Refresh:** The first question changed to "During computer class...".
- **Second Refresh:** The first question changed to "I helped my neighbor...".

This confirms that the questions are being shuffled correctly at the start of each session.
